5:
Here we are, the forest where the
ashen monster was spotted.
8:
An ashen monster that sends its
prey into deep slumber, a state with
no known cure as of yet...
13:
We can't just let it be! I'll slay the
monster myself if I have to!
18:
Are you okay?! Good thing you're
not hurt too badly. Is anyone else
with you?
20:
*sniff* It's just me. Mommy and
Daddy won't wake up, so I was
gathering herbs for them...
22:
I figured with the right medicine,
maybe they could wake up from
that pale ghost's curse.
28:
I assume it's the very same ashen
monster we seek. And this girl's
parents are its victims.
36:
It's far too dangerous to be alone in
the forest right now. We'll take you
back to the village.
40:
I can't stand the thought of Mommy
and Daddy never waking up again!
So I'm going to keep doing what I
can!
43:
Well... Can you imagine how worried
your parents would be if you're not
around when they wake up?
46:
Leave the herbs to us. Stay by your
parents' side in the meanwhile.
59:
Alk... Our priority should be getting
the girl back to the village. Let us
make haste.
65: Oh no... Not this guy again!
71:
We'll have to carve an opening and
then buy time for the child to
escape.
91:
No thanks needed. I'm just glad I
made it in time.
95:
Oh yeahI haven't introduced
myself yet! I'm Alk, and this here's
99:
Light. We thank you for your
assistance.
104:
I'm Olivia. What brings you three out
here?
112:
And that about sums it up. We were
escorting the kid home.
117: I'm sorry. This is all my fault.
124:
The ashen savior is the true culprit. I
managed to chase him down at
one point but failed to finish the job.
130:
Upon our arrival in this new world, he
quickly began his quest of what he
considers to be salvation.
132:
He unleashed his ashen monsters
onto the land, attacking people and
draining their mana.
134:
Those attacked fall into deep
slumberlikely a result of the
sudden loss of mana.
141:
I must continue searching for the
ashen savior. If I can finish him off,
his victims will awaken.
146:
Sounds like we have a common
enemy! Let us help you!
150:
I appreciate the sentiment, but I
would rather not drag you into a
situation that I am solely
responsible for.
161:
We may not be as strong as you, but
we can't just sit around while people
are in danger.
165:
I'm sure we'll come in handy. Let us
join you!
170: I see how determined you are...
174: Very well. Lend me your strength.
178:
We can start by asking around at
the Guild.
182:
Yes, looking into the areas that were
attacked and gathering eyewitness
accounts should give us a lead.
190:
I'll look into the situation while the
rest of you usher the child to safety.
201:
...I promise to save your parents as
well.
